file=Brand Studio/rio/custom/ad-platform-mechanics/assets/ad-platform-playbook-template.md · [pp:[Ad Platform] Playbook — [Brand] — TEMPLATE (the volatile paid layer)=> Designed to go stale visibly: every entry dated; entries older than the review cadence are\n> suspect until re-confirmed. One per ad platform per brand, at rio's config\n> `ad_platform_playbooks/`. Refresh sources: operator observations, kai's reconciled data,\n> the shared research layer when built. Durable principles live in the SKILL.md, not here.\n\n**Platform:** [name] \· **Brand:** [name] \· **Last full review:** [YYYY-MM-DD]\n**Review cadence:** [from rio-config]\n · 1ts:1. Tracking setup state *(dated)*=- Pixel/server-side status: [verified end-to-end on …; events covered: …]\n- Attribution settings in force: [window, click/view basis — must match rio-config `attribution_basis`]\n · tb=\| Format \| Specs \| Performance notes (kai-reconciled) \| As of \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · 3a&:3. Auction & delivery notes *(dated, most volatile)*=[Bidding options in use, learning-phase thresholds observed, placement quirks — observations, not physics.]\n · 4cr:4. Creative refresh cadence *(dated)*=[Fatigue curve observed for this account: rotate at ~N weeks / frequency ~X]\n · 5p&:5. Policy & jurisdiction lines=[Platform ad policies relevant to this business; operator-supplied jurisdiction rules\n(e.g., Canadian advertising standards, category restrictions). Violations are refusals, not optimizations.]\n · 6d*:6. Don'ts *(dated)*=[Account-specific learned failures]\n · tb=\| Date \| What changed \| Source (operator / kai / research) \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|